11#ifndef MODULES_PACING_PACKET_ROUTER_H_
12#define MODULES_PACING_PACKET_ROUTER_H_

14#include <stddef.h>
15#include <stdint.h>
16
17#include <list>
18#include <memory>
19#include <unordered_map>
20#include <utility>
21#include <vector>
22
23#include "api/transport/network_types.h"
24#include "modules/pacing/pacing_controller.h"
25#include "modules/remote_bitrate_estimator/include/remote_bitrate_estimator.h"

30#include "rtc_base/synchronization/mutex.h"
31#include "rtc_base/thread_annotations.h"
32
33namespace webrtc {
34
35class RtpRtcpInterface;
36
37// PacketRouter keeps track of rtp send modules to support the pacer.
38// In addition, it handles feedback messages, which are sent on a send
39// module if possible (sender report), otherwise on receive module
40// (receiver report). For the latter case, we also keep track of the
41// receive modules.
42class PacketRouter : public PacingController::PacketSender {
43 public:
44 PacketRouter();
45 explicit PacketRouter(uint16_t start_transport_seq);
46 ~PacketRouter() override;
47
48 void AddSendRtpModule(RtpRtcpInterface* rtp_module, bool remb_candidate);
49 void RemoveSendRtpModule(RtpRtcpInterface* rtp_module);
50
51 void AddReceiveRtpModule(RtcpFeedbackSenderInterface* rtcp_sender,
52 bool remb_candidate);
53 void RemoveReceiveRtpModule(RtcpFeedbackSenderInterface* rtcp_sender);
54
55 void SendPacket(std::unique_ptr<RtpPacketToSend> packet,
56 const PacedPacketInfo& cluster_info) override;
57 std::vector<std::unique_ptr<RtpPacketToSend>> FetchFec() override;
58 std::vector<std::unique_ptr<RtpPacketToSend>> GeneratePadding(
59 DataSize size) override;
60
61 uint16_t CurrentTransportSequenceNumber() const;
62
63 // Send REMB feedback.
64 void SendRemb(int64_t bitrate_bps, std::vector<uint32_t> ssrcs);
65
66 // Sends |packets| in one or more IP packets.
67 void SendCombinedRtcpPacket(
68 std::vector<std::unique_ptr<rtcp::RtcpPacket>> packets);
69
70 private:
71 void AddRembModuleCandidate(RtcpFeedbackSenderInterface* candidate_module,
72 bool media_sender)
73 RTC_EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(modules_mutex_);
74 void MaybeRemoveRembModuleCandidate(
75 RtcpFeedbackSenderInterface* candidate_module,
76 bool media_sender) RTC_EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(modules_mutex_);
77 void UnsetActiveRembModule() RTC_EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(modules_mutex_);
78 void DetermineActiveRembModule() RTC_EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(modules_mutex_);
79 void AddSendRtpModuleToMap(RtpRtcpInterface* rtp_module, uint32_t ssrc)
80 RTC_EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(modules_mutex_);
81 void RemoveSendRtpModuleFromMap(uint32_t ssrc)
82 RTC_EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(modules_mutex_);
83
84 mutable Mutex modules_mutex_;
85 // Ssrc to RtpRtcpInterface module;
86 std::unordered_map<uint32_t, RtpRtcpInterface*> send_modules_map_
87 RTC_GUARDED_BY(modules_mutex_);
88 std::list<RtpRtcpInterface*> send_modules_list_
89 RTC_GUARDED_BY(modules_mutex_);
90 // The last module used to send media.
91 RtpRtcpInterface* last_send_module_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(modules_mutex_);
92 // Rtcp modules of the rtp receivers.
93 std::vector<RtcpFeedbackSenderInterface*> rtcp_feedback_senders_
94 RTC_GUARDED_BY(modules_mutex_);
95
96 // Candidates for the REMB module can be RTP sender/receiver modules, with
97 // the sender modules taking precedence.
98 std::vector<RtcpFeedbackSenderInterface*> sender_remb_candidates_
99 RTC_GUARDED_BY(modules_mutex_);
100 std::vector<RtcpFeedbackSenderInterface*> receiver_remb_candidates_
101 RTC_GUARDED_BY(modules_mutex_);
102 RtcpFeedbackSenderInterface* active_remb_module_
103 RTC_GUARDED_BY(modules_mutex_);
104
105 uint64_t transport_seq_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(modules_mutex_);
106
107 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/10809): Replace lock with a sequence checker once the
108 // process thread is gone.
109 std::vector<std::unique_ptr<RtpPacketToSend>> pending_fec_packets_
110 RTC_GUARDED_BY(modules_mutex_);
111
112 RTC_DISALLOW_COPY_AND_ASSIGN(PacketRouter);
113};
114} // namespace webrtc
115#endif // MODULES_PACING_PACKET_ROUTER_H_
